# Inter-Agent Communication Policy

Publish structured events to the shared company intercom so the Chief of Staff can aggregate status across products.

## Shared location

`C:/Users/b06xo/OneDrive/Test/intercom/`

(Equivalent path reference: `/test/intercom/`)

Write one JSON file per meaningful event. Do not commit intercom files into application repos.

## Filename convention

`YYYYMMDDTHHMMSSZ__{product}__{agentSlug}__{eventType}__{correlationId}.json`

Example: `20260714T102015Z__Problems4Us__autonomous-team__milestone__a1b2c3d4.json`

## Required fields

```json
{
  "agentName": "Problems4Us Autonomous Digital Business Team",
  "product": "Problems4Us",
  "project": "workstream-name",
  "timestampUtc": "2026-07-14T10:20:15Z",
  "eventType": "work.completed",
  "severity": "Info",
  "currentTask": "Short task title",
  "status": "Completed",
  "humanActionRequired": null,
  "correlationId": "stable-id-for-this-thread-of-work",
  "summary": "One-line summary",
  "message": "Detailed message for aggregation and audit."
}
```

### Allowed values

- **product**: `DTS` | `XPS` | `Problems4Us`
- **severity**: `Info` | `Warning` | `Error` | `Critical`
- **status**: `Started` | `Progress` | `Completed` | `Blocked` | `Failed` | `Waiting`

## When to emit

Emit on meaningful state changes only:

- Starting work
- Completing work
- Becoming blocked
- Recovering from an error
- Requesting human approval
- Finishing a milestone
- Detecting a risk
- Encountering repeated failures
- Changing operational state (idle, running, waiting)

Do **not** emit for every file edit or routine intermediate step.

## Problems4Us defaults

- **agentName**: `Problems4Us Autonomous Digital Business Team`
- **product**: `Problems4Us`
- Keep one `correlationId` for a user-requested workstream until it completes or fails.
